<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4653282>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Reproductive anatomy of Austrochloritis porteri. (A–C) Drawings showing the entire reproductive system: (A) AM C.363835 (NSW, Upper Richmond River); (B) AM C.575455 (NSW, Mt Warning); (C) AM C.512605 (Queensland, Lamington NP). Scale bars = 5 mm. (D–F) Details of penial anatomy: (D) AM C.363835 (NSW, Upper Richmond River); (E) AM C.575455 (NSW, Mt Warning); (F) AM C.512605 (Queensland, Lamington NP). Scale bars = 3 mm.Abbreviations: ag—albumen gland; at—atrium; bc—bursa copulatirx; ep—epiphallus; fl—epiphallic flagellum; hd—hermaphroditic duct; ipw—inner penial wall; p—penis; pm—penial retractor; pv—penial verge; va—vagina; vd—vas deferens." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4653282/files/figure.png" .

